Zodidi Mhlana JOHANNESBURG- Nine people died in a crash that involved two vehicles in Mbombela, Mpumalanga on Monday morning. According to traffic authorities, seven people were burnt beyond recognition during the accident. Provincial Community Safety spokesperson that the number of people who have died might rise during the course of the day. “The cars caught fire and most of the people were burnt beyond recognition. It was a head on collision that was caused by one driver who lost control of his vehicle and it collided with the vehicle that was coming from the opposite direction,” he said. He said the families of the deceased have been notified about the accident. Mabuza said that the crash occurred on the N4 road at around 03h05 at Karino. He said that both vehicles caught fire @Mhlana
